# Demo Showcase three-layer boundary — IDE anti-drift contract

**Canonical decision:** [ADR-0041](../../docs/decisions/0041-demo-showcase-three-lanes.md) (AGENTS.md **PRIORITY #2**) · Layer 1 seal: [`app/(main)/[locale]/demo/_SEAL.md`](../../app/(main)/[locale]/demo/_SEAL.md)

**If this rule and `AGENTS.md` diverge, follow `AGENTS.md` and fix this rule in the same PR.**

Local public showcase uses **one product name everywhere: `demo`**.

Mechanical guard: [`tests/unit/demo-route-contract.test.ts`](../../tests/unit/demo-route-contract.test.ts)

---

## Prime directive

```txt
Layer 1 — app/           → URL + thin re-exports ONLY
Layer 2 — lib/features/  → manifest, gate, fixtures, guides, page orchestrators
Layer 3 — components2/   → DemoShell, DemoGuidePanel, banner, catalog chrome ONLY
```

**Import doors:**

| Layer | Door |
| --- | --- |
| Layer 2 | `#features/demo` · `#features/demo/server` |
| Layer 3 | `#components2/demo/*` |
| Client-safe paths + types | `#features/demo/client` (`demoPath`, manifest types, `DemoBanner`) |

---

## Lane A vs Lane B

| Lane | URL | Data |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **A — Demo Showcase** | `/{locale}/demo/*` | Fixture SSOT in `lib/features/demo/data/*.fixture.server.ts` |
| **B — Portal / ERP** | `/p/*`, `/o/*` | Real tenant after `pnpm dev:seed` + `pnpm dev:seed:demo-erp` |

**Forbidden on Lane A:** `requireOrgSession`, `requirePortalContext`, `#lib/db`, production page re-exports (`EmployeePortalLeavePage`, `WorkforcePage`, …).

**Allowed cross-module read:** list-surface **builders** and **types** from `#features/hrm/server` (and similar) when demo mirrors a governed Pattern C surface — never production orchestrators.

---

## Layer 1 — `app/.../demo/`

**Allowed in leaf `page.tsx`:**

```tsx
export { DemoEmployeeLeavePage as default } from "#features/demo/server"
```

**Forbidden:** fixtures, `DemoGuidePanel` wiring, `redirectIfDemoShowcaseDisabled`, `#components2/demo` in routes.

---

## Layer 2 — `lib/features/demo/`

- **`schemas/demo-route-manifest.shared.ts`** — catalog SSOT; `status: "available"` only when `app/.../demo/<slug>/page.tsx` exists.
- **`data/demo-route-gate.server.ts`** — dev always on; prod needs `NEXT_PUBLIC_AFENDA_DEMO_SHOWCASE=1`.
- **`data/guides/*.shared.ts`** — usage guide copy for `DemoGuidePanel`.
- **`components/demo-*-page.server.tsx`** — compose `DemoShell` + `DemoSurfaceLayout` + read-only surface + `DemoRelatedDemos`.

**Forbidden:** `_SEAL.md` at `lib/features/demo/` root (check-agent-contract).

---

## Layer 3 — `components2/demo/`

Presentation only: shell, banner, guide panel, catalog card, layout slots.

**Forbidden:** DB access, ERP mutations, session guards.

---

## Product Operating Manual formula

Every **available** manifest entry should ship:

1. Thin `app/.../demo/<slug>/page.tsx` re-export
2. Fixture rows + optional builder reuse from production modules
3. `DemoGuidePanel` content (`data/guides/`)
4. `DemoBanner` + related demo links

---

## Verify after edits

```bash
pnpm lint:path -- lib/features/demo components2/demo app/(main)/[locale]/demo
pnpm test:fast -- tests/unit/demo-route-contract.test.ts
```
